Environment: Windows 11
Shell: PowerShell

Rules:
1. Use semicolon (;) for command chaining, not &&
2. Use forward slashes (/) in code paths
3. Test commands before suggesting
4. Prefer npm scripts over direct commands
5. When using Bash tool in Cursor, ensure proper escaping for Windows
6. Use Next.js 15 App Router conventions
7. Prefer TypeScript over JavaScript for type safety
8. Use ESM imports (import/export) not CommonJS (require/module.exports)

RAG Pipeline Testing Requirements:
9. Each phase of the RAG pipeline MUST have a dedicated test endpoint
   - Test endpoints allow testing without generating embeddings or calling external APIs
   - Enables rapid iteration and debugging without incurring API costs
   - All test endpoints require ADMIN_SECRET authentication
   - Test endpoints should return detailed debugging information
10. Current test endpoints:
    - /api/ai/test-pdfs - Test PDF loading and parsing
    - /api/ai/test-pdf-parsing - Test PDF parsing with section detection
    - /api/ai/test-chunking - Test document chunking strategies
    - Future: test-embeddings, test-vector-search, test-llm endpoints
